<item>
            <title>[HBASE-452] &quot;region offline&quot; should throw IOException, not IllegalStateException</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-452</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It would be nice if I could wrap my HTable.get calls in try {} catch (IOException e).  But that doesn&apos;t work, since I also need to catch IllegalStateException.  I think that any time there is something wrong with hbase, hbase calls should throw an IOException (or subclass thereof).  Things like IllegalStateException should be reserved for programmer error.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12388816">HBASE-452</key>
            <summary>&quot;region offline&quot; should throw IOException, not IllegalStateException</summary>
